The President convened a conference call with Department of Defense and FBI leadership to receive an update on the shooting at Fort Hood. He commended the military personnel, first responders, and medical staff for their heroic actions. The President directed his team to fully investigate the shooting and ensure the community has the resources needed to recover. The Department of Defense is leading the investigation with support from federal partners, including the FBI. The President will continue to receive updates and provide assistance to the families affected. The President and First Lady expressed their condolences to the families and friends of the victims.